article.description: Kendle Moore made four 3-pointers and scored 26 points and Colorado State beat Division II Colorado Christian 100-66 on Wednesday night.
article.headline: Moore with 26 leads Colorado St. past Colo. Christian 100-66
article.linkText: Moore with 26 leads Colorado St. past Colo. Christian 100-66
article.story: FORT COLLINS, Colo. -- Kendle Moore made four 3-pointers and scored 26 points and Colorado State beat Division II Colorado Christian 100-66 on Wednesday night. Moore was 9 of 11 from the field for the Rams, who played their first game under new head coach Niko Medved. Anthony Masinton-Bonner added 22 points, five rebounds and four assists, Lorenzo Jenkins had 15 points and six rebounds and Nico Carvacho had 14 points with a team-high 15 rebounds. The Rams shot 52 percent compared to 34.5 for Colorado Christian and outrebounded the Cougars 49-25. Moore made two 3-pointers and three layups as part of a 26-3 start for the Rams and they led all the way to a 53-29 advantage at the break. Collin Huun scored 21 points off the bench on six 3-pointers to lead the Cougars. Justin Engesser had nine points with six rebounds.
